Detailed Description

For details, refere the the constructor documentation.

This class is not to be confused with MapStoreTrace::MapIt.

Construct beam iterator through a MapStore.

This convenient structure encapsulates an instance of the MapStoreBeam class to trace a beam from cell (x1, y1) to cell (x2, y2). For allowed values see the documentation of class MapStoreBeam.

The iterator is created for the map a_map and has a dependency to the map a_map. The map may not be destroyed while this iterator exists. Modifying the map (including growing it) is fine.

Parameters
x1,y1Start cells of beam. The beam originates at the center of the named cell.
x2,y2End cells of beam. The beam terminates at the center of the named cell.

bool mapstore::MapStore::MapIt::next ( int &  x,
int &  y,
double &  val 
)
inline

Return next cell in the trace.

this function determines the next cell in the trace and updates the functions parameters to refelct the next cell. It returns "true" if there was a next cell, and "false" if the end of the trace had been reached. In case of returning "false", the values of the parameters are undefined.

Parameters
xReturn parameter, the functions set x to the x-coordinate of the next cell.
yReturn parameter, the functions set y to the y-coordinate of the next cell.
valReturn parameter, the function sewt val to the next cell's value.
Return values
truex, y and val have been updated.
falseThe last cell has been reached (in the previous call). The return parameters are undefined.
